Bug.WithStack:
If the "Extract Local Variable" refactoring is used inside a loop with a single
statement and omitted braces, the recatoring fails or results in incorrect code
when forced to.

Before:

  private void method() {
    for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
      System.out.println(i * i);
  }

After: 
(the "i * i" expression was extracted into the local variable "isquared")

  private void method() {
    int isquared = i * i;
    for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
      System.out.println(isquared);
  }
Move to JDT/UI


